sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpA-HIVcl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: OmpA + HIV protease cleavage site secretion system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This device is designed for the further incorporation of any protein coding sequence downstream the HIV cleavage site. Upon addition of arabinose to the medium, the inducible Pbad promoter drives the expression of outer membrane protein A (ompA) fused to a extracellular linker followed by a cleavage site recognizable by HIV protease.
If any polypeptide sequence is fused to the 3?? end of the HIV cleavage site DNA sequence, it will protrude from the outer membrane where it will be cleaved from the ompA domain by HIV protease.
By this means, this device works as a arabinose -> protein secretion system.
